 ## Recurring Gotchas
 <!-- Problems encountered repeatedly; save future tracks from the same pain -->
 
 ## Patterns That Worked Well
-<!-- Approaches worth repeating -->
 - `validate_field` + `validate_config` pattern: field-level validators composed into a full-config validator ‚Äî easy to test in isolation and extend per section.
 - Error border via tk.Frame `highlightbackground` + `highlightthickness` ‚Äî cleaner than ttk styling for dynamic error states.
+- Per-widget error state (show_error/clear_error) wired via on_change callback chain ‚Äî works consistently across Entry, Combo, Spinbox, Check.
 
 ## Implementation Notes
-<!-- Notes about constraint fields naming -->
 - Plan spec uses `min`/`max`/`choices` but implementation uses `min_value`/`max_value`/`enum_values` ‚Äî semantics are identical, just naming difference. No refactoring needed.
 - Widget error state uses wrapper tk.Frame with red highlightborder around the inner ttk widget.
+- Validation state (_validation_errors) maintained in main.py and updated via _update_validation_state() on every change, load, and after _collect_from_tabs.
 
 ## Planning Improvements
-<!-- Notes on where estimates were wrong and why -->
+- Phase 3 (Save Guard & Status Bar): 3 tasks completed in one session ‚Äî status bar label, save button disable/enable, and integration tests.
 - Phase 6 (Polish) tasks were smaller than Phase 1-5 (Schema + Widgets) ‚Äî 4 tasks completed in one session vs multi-session phases earlier.
 - Phase 6.1-6.3 (validation, status bar, variable preview) were already implemented before Phase 6 started ‚Äî plan was ahead of marks.
 - Phase 2 (Widget Error States): 4 tasks completed in one session ‚Äî show_error/clear_error pattern is consistent across widget types.

